  "text": "where W is a diagonal matrix, containing the w i 's along its diagonal. Weighting the loss function with w i is equivalent to weighting each single data point x i and output y i with √ w i [CITATION_1] . The same reformulation also holds for the dimensionality-reduction methods discussed below [CITATION_2] .",
